            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.514285683631897,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "[h1]An old (2004) but classic RTS & Battle Simulator game that has been delisted/discontinued from Steam.\n\nThe complete edition comes with the first, [i]Barbarian Invasion[/i] (2005) expansion pack.\nMultiplayer is dead but still works, and can't go wrong LAN or single player. \n\nI suck at these games but now it's a relic on my account!\n\n7/10[/h1]"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226918059",
            "steam_id": "76561198746713566",
            "playtime_minutes": 5857,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "If you enjoy the Glory of Rome. managing cities and troops in the field of battle this is a must for the keyboard general,"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226061178",
            "steam_id": "76561198288392213",
            "playtime_minutes": 2553,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Well, this game is my Roman Empire and a classic in the RTS genre. It really is good and interesting. Playing it again from time to time is always a pleasure, and it also happens to be my very first strategy game. And as I say it often, nothing beats the \"first\"."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "225880480",
            "steam_id": "76561198041621948",
            "playtime_minutes": 34424,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "This game hits the sweet spot for me.  Not too hard.  Not too complicated.  Just right."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "225699888",
            "steam_id": "76561198062004021",
            "playtime_minutes": 94911,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "It's addicting! The game is just so simple to learn, and it has great replayability value, especially if you are a big fan of all of the Total War games!"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "225610639",
            "steam_id": "76561198190265858",
            "playtime_minutes": 1415,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "I love this game and always have since it first came out. I just wish I could fix the lagging caused by it being on a modern computer. Sadly downloading DXWrapper and the d3dll didn't seem to work unless I did it wrong. It's a shame because this game like the original Medieval Total war or Sid Meiers Colonization or Sid Meiers 1,2,3, ad 4 and some of the best strategy games ever made."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "225227066",
            "steam_id": "76561198367153695",
            "playtime_minutes": 239,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "One of the best games I have ever played. Worth every penny.\r\nIf you choose fighting on the battlefield, be prepared for quite a long time (especially when the forces are evenly matched)."
        },
        {
